```ts
async function avgA0(device, n = 16) {
  let s = 0
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) s += await device.pin('A0').read()
  return s / n
}
```

JavaScript has `Array.prototype.reduce`, no `analogRead`. Each loop iteration awaits a real device round trip.

```ts
import { ConduytDevice } from 'conduyt-js'
import { BLETransport } from 'conduyt-js/transports/ble'

const device = await ConduytDevice.connect(
  new BLETransport({ name: 'Sense' })
)

const v = await device.pin('A0').read()
console.log('A0', v)
```

You do not call `BLE.begin()` from the host. That is an Arduino sketch primitive that lives on the chip.
